	 New Delhi, Sept. 19: The government is confident about meeting the indirect tax collection target of Rs 3.2 lakh crore during 2008-09 despite tardy growth in excise duty mop-up because of duty cuts on petrol and diesel and misuse of exemptions.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 19: Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) will invest Rs 7,000 crore in this fiscal as part of its capital expenditure. It plans to increase its refining capacity to 80 million tonnes per annum from 60.2 million tonnes by 2011-12.                            
	 Mumbai, Sept. 19: Emami today rescheduled the open offer date for acquiring an additional 20 per cent stake in Zandu Pharmaceutical. The offer will begin on September 26 and close on October 15.                                                                                                                         
